The paper discusses the need for an automated data exploration service in database systems, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The proposed framework, AIDE, relies on classification algorithms and optimization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework also involves user interaction and feedback, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
